description: Sameer Khan, son-in-law of NCP member Nawab Malik, died from injuries after a tragic accident in September caused by a driver error. Despite intensive care, Khan succumbed to a severe brain clot. Nawab Malik confirmed the news and announced a halt to public engagements for two days.
title: Nawab Malik's son-in-law who was hit by own SUV in September dies

description: Stones were thrown at the Vande Bharat Express near Khurja junction, damaging a window glass on Sunday morning. Railway Protection Force officials have registered an FIR and believe children might be involved. Nagina MP Chandra Shekhar Azad condemned the incident, emphasizing the risks to passenger safety and the financial toll on Railways.
title: Stones hurled at Vande Bharat in UP, FIR filed against rowdies

description: Mumbai police detained a woman for allegedly sending a threatening message to Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath via the city’s traffic police WhatsApp helpline. The suspect, Fatima Khan, was released after her family cited mental health issues and was asked to provide medical records. Police believe the threat may be a hoax.
title: Maharashtra woman held for hoax death threat to UP CM, let off

description: Manipur celebrated its traditional Ningol Chakouba festival, inviting married sisters for a family feast. Displaced women, including those in relief camps, participated with hopes of future celebrations at home. Organizations facilitated gatherings, fostering communal harmony and peace, especially for those affected by last year's unrest.
title: After a year's hiatus, festival brings cheer in strife-torn Manipur

description: Several Kerala cadre IAS officers were added to a WhatsApp group named 'Mallu Hindu Officers,' reportedly created from the number of IAS officer K Gopalakrishnan, who claimed his phone was hacked. The group, seen as contrary to secular principles, prompted a police complaint and investigations by intelligence agencies.
title: WhatsApp group for 'Mallu Hindu' IAS officers stirs row, deleted later

description: The appointments of advocates Saurabh Kirpal, R John Satyan, Amitesh Banerjee, and Sakya Sen as HC judges remain pending with the government, despite reiterated recommendations by the Supreme Court collegium. Justice Sanjiv Khanna will succeed as the next Chief Justice of India on November 11, 2023.
title: No forward movement on 4 names reiterated by collegium headed by CJI Chandrachud

description: A 90-year-old report by RC Morris on elephant deaths due to Kodo millet poisoning in Tamil Nadu, detailing antidotes like tamarind water and buttermilk, is being reconsidered as 10 elephants recently died under similar circumstances in Bandhavgarh Tiger Reserve.
title: 1934 report on deaths of 14 elephants in Tamil Nadu in 1933 puts focus on possible antidotes

description: Karnataka BJP plans to submit a ground report about waqf notices and property record mutations in Vijayapura to a joint parliamentary committee. Despite Chief Minister Siddaramaiah's directive to cancel waqf entries in farmers' land records, BJP aims to emphasize this issue. The committee is led by BJP's Jagadambika Pal.
title: BJP to send waqf 'ground report' to joint parliamentary committee

description: Facing pressure from farmers and opposition parties over the waqf property controversy, Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah orders officials to revoke changes to farmers' land deeds. He asserts that previous administrations, including BJP and JD(S), have issued similar notifications and accuses BJP of hypocrisy and stirring communal sentiments.
title: Recall notices sent to farmers on waqf land, says Karnataka CM Sidda

description: Canadian MP Chandra Arya condemned the attack by pro-Khalistani extremists on Hindu-Canadian devotees at the Brampton Hindu Sabha temple, highlighting extremists exploiting freedom of expression. Peel Regional Police and Brampton Mayor Patrick Brown assure maintaining public order and safety amid increased tensions between Canadian and Indian governments.
title: Canadian MP Chandra Arya condemns Khalistanis attack on Hindu temple in Brampton, police starts investigation

description: A court in UP's Ambedkar Nagar has ordered the reopening of a murder case against eight policemen for the custodial death of Ziauddin in 2021, rejecting the police's claim of a heart attack. The order is based on injury marks found in the postmortem report.
title: Reopen case against 8 cops for custodial death of Ziauddin in 2021: UP court

description: A gas leak incident at Royal Marine Shrimp Processing Unit in Nizampatnam, Andhra Pradesh, resulted in 107 workers experiencing respiratory issues after mistakenly combining hydrochloric acid with sodium hypochlorite. The release of chlorine gas caused initial symptoms in 30 workers, later affecting more. Authorities are investigating for potential negligence.
title: 107 workers fall ill after gas leak at Andhra Pradesh shrimp processing unit

description: A 10-year-old tiger identified as T-86 was killed by villagers in retaliation after it attacked and killed a 45-year-old man near Ranthambore National Park. The incident sparked protests, leading to mediation by the Rajasthan agriculture minister. Local forest monitoring gaps have been highlighted.
title: A day after it mauled man, tiger killed by Rajasthan villagers

description: Madhya Pradesh CM Mohan Yadav suspended officials for negligence over the deaths of 10 elephants in Umaria district and announced an Elephant Task Force to promote coexistence. Compensation for loss of life was increased from Rs 8 lakh to Rs 25 lakh per person.
title: Two Bandhavgarh officials suspended over jumbo deaths

description: Prime Minister Modi commended the decline in TB incidence in India, attributing it to dedicated efforts and innovative initiatives. Health Minister J P Nadda highlighted WHO's recognition of a 17.7% decline in TB incidence from 2015 to 2023 and outlined initiatives like the Ni-Kshay Poshan Yojana and BPaLM regimen.
title: Will ensure a tuberculosis-free India through collective spirit: PM Modi

description: Maharashtra's share in India's GDP has decreased from 15.2% in 2010-11 to 13.3% in 2023-24, according to an EAC-PM paper. In contrast, Gujarat's share has risen from 7.5% to 8.1% during the same period. Maharashtra still maintains the highest GDP share among states.
title: Maharashtra share in GDP highest, but 2% dip from FY11 to FY24: Study

description: Kamala Harris leads Donald Trump in conservative Iowa according to a new Selzer poll, putting her at 47% compared to Trump's 44%. Trump criticized the poll and its methodology, calling it biased. However, pollster Ann Selzer defended her historical accuracy. Nate Silver also noted the poll's boldness but expressed skepticism about its accuracy.
title: Donald Trump reacts to shocking Iowa poll, calls Ann Selzer a 'hater'

description: Taylor Swift celebrated her relationship with Travis Kelce during a concert in Indianapolis by altering lyrics to a song, referencing Kelce. Fans were thrilled by her gesture. Kelce was seen with Swift's mother at the event. The couple, who confirmed their relationship in September 2023, continues to show support for each other's careers.
title: Taylor Swift’s Playful Shoutout to Travis Kelce Sparks Debate

description: Union home minister Amit Shah unveils BJP’s Jharkhand election manifesto, promising a uniform civil code with tribal exemptions. He accuses illegal Bangladeshi immigrants of taking tribal land and vows to deport them. Other pledges include tribal land protection, reservation reforms, and support for unemployed youth, women, and farmers.
title: BJP vows UCC in Jharkhand, says will keep tribals out of ambit

description: At least 12 people were injured in a grenade attack in a busy Srinagar market near the Tourist Reception Centre. The attack created panic among shoppers just a day before the J&K assembly session. The grenade, aimed at a security vehicle, missed its target. Police have launched a search for the terrorists responsible.
title: Grenade attack in Srinagar Sunday market leaves 12 wounded

description: Delhi's air quality worsened significantly on Sunday, with the AQI rising from 316 to 382, the highest in nine months. Calm winds and low temperatures hindered pollutant dispersion. Experts predict air quality will remain in the 'very poor' category until Wednesday. South-easterly winds will likely reduce stubble burning's contribution to pollution.
title: Delhi air close to ‘severe’, worst in over 9 months

description: CPM deputy leader in Rajya Sabha, John Brittas, has protested against junior minister Ravneet Singh's use of Hindi in official replies, citing it contravenes conventions and the Official Languages Act. Brittas responded in Malayalam, emphasizing that Kerala hasn't adopted Hindi as an official language, impacting MPs from non-Hindi-speaking regions.
title: CPM’s Brittas protests Hindi responses from minister, replies in Malayalam

description: Varun Dhawan appeared on 'Kaun Banega Crorepati 16' where a question about actress Zubeida led to controversy. The show's producers and Amitabh Bachchan mistakenly attributed Zubeida's biography to another individual, leading to criticism from her son, Khalid Mohammed, and social media users for the research inaccuracy.
title: KBC 16: Netizens catch the recent goof up over a ques on Maharaj Hanwant Singh's wife

description: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce's romance blossomed in September 2023, capturing fans' attention. On November 2, Kelce was seen at Swift’s Eras Tour concert in Indianapolis, where he sat with Swift's mother and danced together. Their supportive relationship sees Swift attending Kelce’s Kansas City Chiefs games and he attending her concerts. The Eras Tour continues in Toronto on November 14.
title: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce enjoy a special night together at the Eras tour

description: ISRO is conducting an analog mission in Ladakh as part of its Gaganyaan program to prepare astronauts for India’s first human spaceflight. The mission will replicate space conditions such as isolation and confinement to study physical, mental, and operational challenges, ensuring astronauts’ readiness for space.
title: What is Isro's 'analog' space mission and what is it's aim?

description: Jammu and Kashmir Lieutenant Governor Manoj Sinha has directed security forces to provide an effective response after a grenade attack injured 11 people in Srinagar's 'Sunday market.' Sinha assured that forces have the freedom to eliminate terror groups. This directive follows CM Omar Abdullah's call for heightened security measures to prevent further attacks and protect civilians.
title: 'Crush terror outfits': J&K LG to security officials post grenade attack
BJP’s ‘secular’ allies Naidu, Nitish must not allow Waqf Bill to be passed in Parliament: Jamiat

description: Donald Trump criticized Democrats for revoking Joe Biden's candidacy, alleging election theft. As the presidential race heats up, polls show a close contest between Kamala Harris and Trump in key swing states like Nevada, North Carolina, Wisconsin, Arizona, Michigan, Georgia, and Pennsylvania, all within a marginal error of 3.5%.
title: Democrats stole election from Biden: Donald Trump

description: Kamala Harris made a surprise appearance on Saturday Night Live, energising her supporters and drawing criticism from Trump followers. The sketch featured humor targeting Trump and the election, with Maya Rudolph impersonating Harris. Celebrity endorsements continue to play a significant role, with stars like Harrison Ford and Arnold Schwarzenegger supporting Harris.
title: Kamala makes a killing on Saturday Night Live amid celebrity rush to back her

description: No one thought it would be this close two days before election day or predicted Trump’s renaissance. Two years ago, Trump appeared to be a lost cause, on the verge of being disqualified, fighting numerous criminal cases, and even rejected by the Republican establishment, which seemed to have found a new knight in shining armour in Ron DeSantis. The New York Post, which recently endorsed Trump, had buried the news about Trump’s re-election bid deep inside.
title: US Election 2024: 10 reasons why this is Donald Trump's race to lose

description: King Felipe VI, Queen Letizia, and Prime Minister Pedro Sánchez faced a hostile reception from flood survivors in Paiporta during their visit. Protestors threw mud, and security interventions were required as frustrations peaked over delayed alerts and slow crisis response. Over 200 lives were lost in the floods, with significant damage to homes.
title: Watch: Crowd hurls mud at Spain's king on visit to flood zone

description: A website error by a Pakistan-based company led thousands to gather for a non-existent Halloween parade in Dublin. Crowds blocked O'Connell Street, expecting a postponed event from Mácnas, before police clarified the mistake. The website operator has apologized for the confusion.
title: Massive turnout for fake Halloween parade leaves Pak company red-faced

description: New York officials seized and euthanized a pet squirrel named Peanut, causing outrage and support for owner Mark Longo. Peanut was a social media sensation and symbol for Longo's animal sanctuary. Authorities cited concerns about rabies, with Peanut allegedly biting an officer. The incident sparked online backlash from public figures, including Elon Musk.
title: Why did New York officials euthanize Peanut the Squirrel?

description: Kamala Harris's presidential campaign diverges from Hillary Clinton's by emphasizing pragmatic policies over breaking gender barriers. Harris focuses on her record and specific issues like immigration reform, avoiding direct clashes with Trump and underplaying her historic candidacy, while grassroots supporters highlight her identity.
title: How Harris’ campaign redefined Hilary Clinton’s playbook against Trump

description: Two Delhi traffic police officers sustained minor injuries after being hit and dragged for 20 metres by a vehicle in a hit-and-run incident near the Ber Sarai traffic signal. The incident took place on Saturday at about 7.45 pm. A case under attempt to murder and other charges has been registered, with an arrest expected soon.
title: Video: Two Delhi cops dragged 20 metres in hit-and-run incident

description: The BCCI is set to review India's poor performance against New Zealand and discuss pitch conditions and team management. Concerns about head coach Gautam Gambhir’s involvement in selection meetings and senior players' participation in domestic cricket will also be addressed. The board aims to develop a clear plan for the team's future, especially with the upcoming Australia tour.
title: Seniors, coaching staff, pitches up for review after whitewash at home

description: In a significant anti-terror operation in downtown Srinagar, security forces neutralized Lashkar-e-Taiba (LeT) commander Usman. The operation included innovative tactics like pacifying stray dogs with biscuits to maintain stealth. Usman, heavily armed, engaged in a day-long gunfight, resulting in his elimination and minor injuries to four personnel.
title: How biscuits helped security forces in operation to eliminate Lashkar-e-Taiba commander

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Basit Ali praised Rishabh Pant for his exceptional performances during India's 3-0 Test series defeat to New Zealand. Pant scored 60 and 64 in challenging conditions, displaying smart shot-selection. Despite his efforts, India struggled against New Zealand's bowling, ultimately collapsing to a 25-run loss in the final Test in Mumbai.
title: 'Pant 50 crore me jana chahye IPL auction me': Basit Ali

description: For the first time, the Indian men's cricket team faced a whitewash in a home Test series of three or more matches, losing 3-0 to New Zealand. Despite strong performances in individual games, collective batting collapses led to the historic series defeat. This setback also dims India's chances for straightforward qualification for the WTC finals.
title: First time in 91 years! How NZ handed India home series drubbing

description: The Iowa poll shows Kamala Harris leading Donald Trump 47-44 in a significant shift just days before the 2024 Presidential election. The survey, by Selzer & Co., highlights a massive swing in female support towards Harris, especially among independent and senior women, largely due to Trump's controversial comments and policies on women's rights.
title: Ayya va! Shock poll in non-battleground state shows Kamala winning

description: Rohit Sharma expressed profound disappointment after India lost 0-3 to New Zealand in the home Test series, marking a historical low. Sharma took responsibility for the team’s performance, highlighting inconsistent batting, especially in the first innings of the initial two Tests, as key factors for the defeat. The series exposed India's vulnerabilities against spin bowling.
title: 'Very low point of my career': Rohit Sharma as India suffer first ever Test series whitewash at home

description: Jason Kelce defended his brother Travis from a fan's homophobic slur outside Beaver Stadium. He grabbed the fan's phone and threw it on the ground. Social media users, including Kansas City Mayor and former NFL player Antonio Brown, supported Jason's actions. Travis Kelce and Taylor Swift were reportedly shocked by the incident.
title: Taylor Swift sparks debate with reaction to homophobic slur aimed at Travis Kelce

description: Shah Rukh Khan's upcoming film King is described as a 'pan-world' project showcasing his global appeal. Vidya Balan humorously questions Kartik Aaryan about his girlfriend. R Madhavan's intense first look for Adhirshtasaali raises excitement. Rajpal Yadav faces criticism for endorsing firecrackers and non-vegetarian products during Diwali. Tanuja avoids paparazzi at Singham Again screening due to health reasons.
title: SRK calls 'King' with Suhana as 'pan-world', Tanuja avoids paps: Top 5 news

description: Anne Arundel County Health Department issued an alert after a raccoon tested positive for Rabies in Shadyside, Maryland. Residents who had contact with raccoons in the area are advised to seek medical attention, as Rabies is fatal if untreated. The symptoms in humans and pets include anxiety, paralysis, and difficulty swallowing. Immediate preventive treatment is crucial.
title: Rabies alert issued in Maryland after raccoon tested positive

description: Sachin Tendulkar reflects on India's unexpected 3-0 series defeat to New Zealand, emphasizing the need for introspection. He commends individual performances by Shubman Gill and Rishabh Pant, while praising New Zealand's consistency and strategy. Ajaz Patel's standout bowling performance played a pivotal role in India's losses, highlighted by his 11-wicket haul.
title: Tendulkar questions India's preparation after whitewash

description: Nawab Malik's son-in-law Sameer Khan passed away at Criticare Hospital following severe injuries from an incident on September 18. Khan sustained a brain clot and multiple fractures after his driver, Abdul Ansari, accidentally hit the accelerator instead of the brakes, crashing into Khan outside a Kurla hospital.
title: Nawab Malik’s son-in-law, in hospital after SUV accident, dies

description: India and China have made progress in disengaging along the Line of Actual Control, particularly at Demchok and Depsang Plains. External affairs minister S Jaishankar highlighted this as a welcome step, following talks between Prime Minister Modi and President Xi. This disengagement may lead to further positive developments in their relationship.
title: 'Other steps could happen': Jaishankar on India-China ties

description: Ajay Devgn's 'Singham Again' has achieved impressive box office success, earning over ₹125 crore worldwide in its first two days since its November 1 release. The film features a star-studded cast, including Kareena Kapoor and Akshay Kumar, and is directed by Rohit Shetty, offering a modern take on the 'Ramayana'.
title: 'Singham Again': Ajay Devgn's film crosses Rs 125 crore

description: In the age of AI, 'silent firing' emerges as a subtle workforce reduction tactic where employers create demoralising conditions causing employees to leave voluntarily. Companies, including Amazon, use this to replace human roles with AI, raising ethical and psychological concerns about its impact on employee morale and job security.
title: What is silent firing companies are using to replace staff with AI

description: BJP has appointed Sunil Sharma, MLA from Padder Nagseni, as the leader of the opposition in the J&K Legislative Assembly. Sharma, who previously served as a minister, won the constituency after the 2022 delimitation, and is focused on expanding the party's presence following the abrogation of Article 370.
title: Meet Sunil Sharma, BJP's first-ever leader of opposition in J&K assembly

description: Actor Vijay's party, Tamilaga Vettri Kazhagam (TVK), passed resolutions against the Centre's NEET exam, the 'One Nation, One Election' initiative, and the Waqf Amendment Bill, while criticizing the DMK government for law and order issues. Vijay aims for TVK to be a major change force in Tamil Nadu, challenging both the BJP and DMK's governance.
title: Actor Vijay's TVK opposes BJP's push for 'One Nation, One Election'

description: S Jaishankar discussed the evolution of Indo-Australian relations, highlighting the significant efforts made. Speaking to the Indian community in Brisbane, he talked about an early conversation with PM Modi in 2014. He emphasised the role of QUAD, education, research, and substantial infrastructure improvements. He also highlighted the role of QUAD, educational cooperation, and significant progress in India.
title: Jaishankar shares story in Brisbane when PM Modi asked him...

description: Reflecting on India's 0-3 Test series defeat to New Zealand, Harbhajan Singh criticized overly spin-friendly pitches. He admitted that while they aimed to challenge New Zealand, the plan backfired, benefiting New Zealand’s bowlers. Harbhajan stressed the need for balanced pitches for competitive cricket. Ajaz Patel’s pivotal 11-wicket haul contributed significantly to New Zealand's historic series win in India.
title: 'Ghaddha khoda aur khud gir gaye': Harbhajan Singh

description: Nawab Malik, a candidate from the Ajit Pawar faction of NCP, refutes allegations linking him to Dawood Ibrahim, calling them defamatory. BJP and Shiv Sena oppose his candidacy due to these allegations, despite being part of the Mahayuti alliance. Malik promises legal action against such accusations.
title: I am candidate of NCP, Mahayuti is against me: Nawab Malik

description: Jammu and Kashmir chief minister described Sunday's grenade attack in Srinagar's 'Sunday market' as 'deeply disturbing,' highlighting the need for urgent security measures. The attack by terrorists targeting a CRPF bunker injured 11 civilians, happening near a heavily fortified area, following the elimination of a prominent Lashkar-e-Taiba commander.
title: 'No justification for targeting innocent civilians': Omar Abdullah on Srinagar grenade attack

description: Sarabhai vs Sarabhai marks its 20th anniversary since premiering on November 1, 2004. The cast, including Deven Bhojani, Rupali Ganguly, and Sumeet Raghavan, celebrated the milestone with a lively Twitter exchange. The sitcom remains beloved, with fans and cast members reminiscing fondly about its impact.
title: Team Sarabhai vs Sarabhai celebrate 2 decades of the show

description: Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3, a comedy thriller featuring Kartik Aaryan and Vidya Balan, has garnered impressive box office success. The film earned ₹36.50 crore on its second day in India and ₹107 crore globally over two days. It achieved a 75.06% theater occupancy rate and received strong responses in major cities.
title: 'Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3': Kartik Aaryan starrer collects Rs 107 Cr

description: In an unprecedented series loss, India suffered a 0-3 whitewash by New Zealand, losing the third Test in Mumbai by 25 runs. Chasing 147, India's batting faltered once again, crumbling to 121 all out. Ajaz Patel's crucial 6-wicket haul and Glenn Phillips' contributions sealed the historic win for New Zealand.
title: 'Most humiliating moment': Team India under fire after shock whitewash

description: Union home minister Amit Shah criticizes Jharkhand CM Hemant Soren for failing to protect tribal communities from alleged infiltrators and promises strong action if BJP wins. Shah claims infiltrators are changing the state's demography, jeopardizing culture, employment, and security. He also calls out discrepancies in Soren's age affidavit, urging transparency.
title: 'Infiltrators who tortured women will be hanged upside down': Amit Shah in Jharkhand

description: Fatima Khan, a 24-year-old IT graduate from Ulhasnagar, Thane district, has been arrested for allegedly threatening to kill Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath. The Mumbai traffic police received the threat on WhatsApp, leading to an investigation by the Anti-Terrorism Squad and Ulhasnagar police, who held Khan responsible.
title: 24-year-old IT graduate behind death threat message to UP CM

description: Nostradamus has been credited with foreseeing numerous historical events, including the Great Fire of London, the rise of Hitler, the French Revolution, the assassination of JFK, the 9/11 attacks, and the Covid-19 pandemic. His quatrains, published in 1555, continue to provoke debate about their prophetic accuracy.
title: Believe it or not, these 'predictions' by Nostradamus 'came true, except ... '

description: Microsoft has appointed Jay Parikh, former global head of engineering at Meta, to its senior leadership team, reporting to CEO Satya Nadella. With extensive experience in building and scaling technical teams, Parikh aims to drive AI innovation and operational excellence at Microsoft. He expresses excitement about Microsoft's vast ambitions, including AI, cloud, gaming, and sustainability.
title: Microsoft hires former head of engineering at Fb: Read CEO Satya Nadella’s note

description: Sandalwood director and actor Guru Prasad, aged 52, was found dead in his Bengaluru apartment on Sunday, with police suspecting financial issues as the cause. Residents reported a foul smell, leading to the discovery of his decomposed body hanging from a ceiling fan. An investigation is underway.
title: Sandalwood director Guru Prasad found dead in Bengaluru apartment

description: In Noida, police arrested Surya Bhadana after a widely circulated video showed him assaulting a woman at Omaxe Palm Green Society. The incident, occurring in the Dari area, depicted Bhadana forcefully grabbing the woman's hair and striking her face. Legal action has been initiated.
title: Viral video: Man slaps female friend at housing society in Noida, arrested
'Bored of PM Modi, why mention again?': Rahul Gandhi after Priyanka slams PM at rally

description: Militants attacked Srinagar's Tourist Reception Centre and weekly Sunday market with a grenade, injuring five. The incident occurred in a crowded flea market near the heavily-guarded TRC. This attack comes after the elimination of a top Pakistani commander of Lashkar-e-Taiba by security forces in Srinagar. The explosion caused panic in the area and sent shoppers scrambling for cover.
title: Militants hurl grenade at TRC, Sunday market in J&K's Srinagar

description: This week's health predictions advise Aries, Leo, and Capricorn to maintain their healthy routines, while Gemini, Taurus, and Virgo may face minor health issues. Women, particularly the pregnant ones, across all signs should avoid risky outdoor activities. Attention to diet, hydration, and stress management is crucial for all zodiac signs.
title: Read your weekly astrological wellness predictions for all zodiac signs

description: A man named Satyanarayana was arrested in Hyderabad for killing a street dog by stabbing it and throwing it from a building after the dog bit his son. The incident was recorded on video, and additional charges may follow for his assault on bystanders.
title: Hyderabad man throws dog off two-storey building for biting his son, held

description: Union home minister Amit Shah unveiled BJP's manifesto for Jharkhand, promising a Uniform Civil Code excluding tribals, addressing Sarna religious code demand, creating 500,000 jobs, investigating paper leaks, reclaiming land from infiltrators, and offering various welfare schemes. Elections are scheduled for November.
title: 'UCC, 5 lakh job opportunities': BJP releases manifesto for Jharkhand polls

description: Sanjay Raut of Shiv Sena (UBT) raised concerns over the enhanced security for Maharashtra home minister Devendra Fadnavis, questioning its necessity. He criticized DGP Rashmi Shukla for alleged bias toward the BJP. Maharashtra Congress President Nana Patole also called for Shukla's removal, citing political violence and partiality in law enforcement.
title: 'Is Israel or Libya going to attack him?': Raut to Fadnavis over increased security

description: New Zealand's Ajaz Patel led a historic 3-0 Test series sweep against India, taking six crucial wickets in the third Test to secure a thrilling 25-run victory. Chasing 147, India crumbled under pressure and were bowled out for 121 at Mumbai’s Wankhede Stadium, marking their first-ever 3-0 defeat at home.
title: 'I was not at my best as captain': Rohit Sharma

description: India faced a historic home defeat by New Zealand, being whitewashed 0-3 in a Test series for the first time in over 24 years. In the final match in Mumbai, India crumbled to 147-run target, despite a fighting half-century by Rishabh Pant. Ajaz Patel's 6/57 sealed the victory for New Zealand.
title: NZ make history as India suffer first ever 0-3 Test series whitewash

description: A couple in Jodhpur killed a 50-year-old beautician, Anita Chaudhary, chopped her body into pieces, and buried it near their house. They lured her for a visit, gave her a sedative-laced drink, stole her jewelry, and then executed their plan to escape debt. The police are searching for the accused husband while his wife has been arrested.
title: Beautician drugged, killed, chopped, and buried by couple over jewellery theft

description: Bigg Boss 18's latest episode sees Ravi Kishan hosting and confronting Rajat Dalal about threatening housemates. Tension rises between Vivian Dsena and Rajat, with heated exchanges about authority and respect. Ravi advises Rajat on handling conflicts, while Avinash Mishra finds humor in the situation, reflecting the show's dramatic and unpredictable nature.
title: Rajat Dalal gets in a tiff with Ravi Kishan over his issues with Vivian

description: The liberal news site Mediaite published an article, now deleted, based on what appeared to be an official press release from Trump’s campaign. This post, which first surfaced on X by user Gentry Genvers, was later clarified as a hoax. Karoline Leavitt, a member of Trump’s team, explained to The Post that it was indeed a “fake statement” and confirmed that Trump “didn’t actually say that,” referring to the post describing Peanut—who had been euthanised after being seized from his upstate New York owners—as “innocent on all accounts” and likening the squirrel to a migrant. Leavitt further dismissed Mediaite as “fake news.”
title: Fact Check: Did Trump condemn death of Peanut the Squirrel?

description: President Joe Biden returned to Pennsylvania to promote Vice President Kamala Harris. He criticised Trump and his supporters during his speech. Biden made comments that stirred reactions online, including a controversial remark about his youth in Scranton. Trump's response at a North Carolina rally added further fuel to the exchange.
title: 'The kind of guys you'd like to smack in the ass': Biden on Trump supporters

description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau shared glimpses from Diwali celebrations with the community, visiting temples and engaging in festivities. He highlighted the festival's message of light over darkness. This comes amid rising tensions between Canada and India, following accusations related to the killing of Hardeep Singh Nijjar.
title: 'Special moments': Trudeau visits temples in Canada to celebrate Diwali

description: An explosion in a general coach of the Howrah Mail near Sirhind railway station in Punjab injured four people. The blast, occurring around 10.30 pm on Saturday, came from a plastic bucket containing firecrackers. The injured were treated at Fatehgarh Sahib Civil Hospital. Authorities are investigating the incident and have sent samples to the Forensic Science Laboratory.
title: 4 injured in explosion in Howrah Mail coach in Punjab

description: A 15-year-old domestic help in Aminjikarai died on Diwali after being brutally assaulted by her employers, Mohammad Nishad and his wife, Nasiya. The couple inflicted severe injuries, including cigarette burns, and locked her in a washroom to die. They, along with other suspects, have been arrested, and police await postmortem results to unveil the full extent of the injuries.
title: 'Branded with iron, cigarette butts': Couple held for murdering teen domestic help

description: India's dominant home run, led by veterans Kohli, Ashwin, Jadeja, and Rohit, ended with a 3-0 series loss to New Zealand. This defeat raises questions about the futures of these ageing stars, with their performances declining and the next home series scheduled for October 2025. The question of their Test future looms large, particularly for home matches.
title: Have we seen last of Virat, Rohit, Ashwin, Jadeja together?

description: A thick layer of smog has engulfed parts of Delhi, with the Air Quality Index (AQI) consistently in the 'very poor' category, reaching hazardous levels. Key areas recorded AQI levels above 350, with some exceeding 400 in the 'severe' range. Delhi's government plans to deploy 200 mobile anti-smog guns to combat the pollution crisis.
title: Delhi air pollution: AQI at 364, residents face difficulty in breathing

description: Ravindra Jadeja's outstanding 10-wicket haul (10/120) in the third Test against New Zealand at Mumbai's Wankhede Stadium boosts India to victory. With five wickets in each innings, Jadeja joins the elite list of Indian bowlers with multiple 10-wicket hauls in Test cricket.
title: Jadeja becomes second Indian to achieve this milestone

description: Senior citizens are increasingly targeted by online scams, involving money transfers. Scammers use impersonation, urgency tactics, and emotional manipulation to deceive victims. To protect themselves, individuals should verify information, use strong passwords, avoid suspicious links, and discuss any concerns with trusted individuals or authorities.
title: Elderly woman loses Rs 50,000 in money transfer scam

description: Mark Longo, owner of a pet squirrel named Peanut, reports a five-hour raid on his home by government agents, seizing his pets. Officials claim Peanut bit someone and must be tested for rabies, but Longo denies it, seeking further investigation. Peanut's rescue story and widespread social media fame highlight his significance to Longo's animal rescue organization.
title: Euthanised squirrel Peanut's owner says his house was ransacked for five hours

description: A disappointing end to the season for Indian cricket stalwarts Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma, as they fail to shine in the home Test series against New Zealand. With lackluster performances, both players struggle to make significant contributions, raising concerns ahead of India's upcoming Test series in Australia.
title: Virat Kohli, Rohit Sharma end home season with a royal disappointment

description: Kamala Harris made a surprise comedic appearance on 'Saturday Night Live' alongside Maya Rudolph, who portrayed her. In their exchange, they humorously discussed shared experiences and took jabs at Donald Trump. The duo, dressed identically, urged supporters to continue backing Harris while ending the segment with the classic 'SNL' sign-off.
title: 'Keep Kamala and carry-on-la': Harris hilarious cameo on 'Saturday Night Live'

description: Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma is accused by the opposition INDIA bloc of using divisive rhetoric against Muslim minorities during a Jharkhand rally. They demand action from the Election Commission, alleging Sarma's remarks incite communal tensions and threaten a fair election process.
title: 'Portrays one minority as infiltrators': Oppn demands action against Assam CM Himanta

description: Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath's security has been increased following a death threat. Mumbai Police received a call warning that Adityanath would face consequences if he didn't step down in 10 days. Authorities are investigating and working to identify the caller behind the threat against the Chief Minister.
title: 'If he doesn't resign in 10 days ... ': Mumbai police receive call threatening UP CM Yogi

description: In Sukma, two policemen were injured in a Naxal attack during a weekly market. They are receiving first aid, and security forces have initiated a search operation. This incident follows recent Naxal violence in Chhattisgarh, including the killing of a man suspected of being a police informer and the encounter that resulted in the death of 38 Naxal cadres.
title: 2 jawans injured in Maoist attack in Chhattisgarh's Sukma

description: A small village in Rajasthan is combatting global warming through a community-driven nursery initiative that distributes indigenous saplings free of cost across Rajasthan, Punjab, and Haryana. The initiative, inspired by familial forestry and supported by international organizations, emphasizes environmental conservation and land restoration.
title: A small village in Rajasthan fights global warming big way

description: The political scenario in Vikhroli assembly constituency sees a complex three-way contest among Sunil Raut of Shiv Sena UBT, Suvarna Karanje of Shiv Sena, and Vishwajit Dholam of MNS. Demographic diversity, local issues like the Kanjurmarg dumping ground, and housing projects significantly influence voter preferences.
title: Division of Marathi votes likely in 3-way poll battle in Mumbai's Vikhroli seat

description: Tom Latham led New Zealand to their first-ever Test series victory in India. Under his calm and methodical captaincy, the Kiwis triumphed in Bengaluru and Pune, even without key player Kane Williamson. Latham's strategies and trust in young players proved instrumental, breaking a long-standing Indian dominance at home. His leadership provided stability and confidence, ensuring the Kiwis made history in India.
title: Will Tom Latham go down in history as one of finest NZ captains?

description: Kamala Harris paid tribute to her mother, Dr Shyamala Gopalan Harris, an Indian immigrant who profoundly influenced her life and career. Harris reflected on her upbringing, her commitment to healthcare equity, her vision for immigration reform, and her foreign policy stance, contrasting it with her opponent's.
title: Kamala Harris draws strength from mother's journey from India

description: Protesters in Dhaka demand protection for Hindus and other minorities facing violence after Sheikh Hasina's ouster. Rally organizers call for minority protection laws and representation. The interim administration acknowledges attacks but claims many are politically motivated. Previous similar protests led to sedition charges against participants.
title: Hundreds march in Dhaka for protection of Hindus, minorities in Bangladesh

description: Jeff Bezos sold over $3 billion worth of Amazon shares, bringing his total stock sales this year to over $13 billion.
title: Jeff Bezos: second richest man after selling Amazon shares worth $3 billion

description: A video of a woman walking in her undergarments at an Iranian university has gone viral, leading to her detention by security. Officials stated she was under mental distress, though some speculate it was a protest against mandatory hijab laws. The woman may be sent to a mental hospital following further investigation.
title: Iranian woman strips in protest over assault by security forces for hijab; arrested

description: Rohit Sharma's performances and leadership have faced criticism after underwhelming Test series against Bangladesh and New Zealand, despite successes in limited-overs formats. His vulnerability to early swing and seam movement is a concern, highlighting the challenges ahead for India and Rohit before the upcoming Australia tour. As India's captain and a senior batsman, there's always pressure to perform and lead by example.
title: How Rohit Sharma's inconsistency with the bat hurt India against NZ

description: Tony Fadell, iPod creator, supports Apple's cautious AI rollout at TechCrunch Disrupt 2024. Fadell highlights its practical benefits, despite initial lukewarm reactions. The iPhone 15 Pro and iPhone 16 models feature early AI tools focusing on practical integration. Apple CEO Tim Cook notes rapid adoption of iOS 18.1, driven by new AI features, with further expansions planned.
title: 'Father of the iPod' defends Apple's AI launch: People are like, “Apple's AI...”

description: India's chances of victory in the final Test against New Zealand will hinge on Virat Kohli's performance on a challenging Wankhede pitch. With New Zealand leading by 143 runs and spinners dominating, Kohli's role is crucial. Despite recent struggles, Kohli's potential match-winning effort could avoid a series whitewash and boost his form for upcoming matches.
title: India need Kohli's experience in crucial run chase vs NZ at Wankhede

description: An analysis by Centre for Science and Environment revealed that Diwali night saw a 34% higher PM2.5 concentration than in 2022, with nitrogen oxide levels also increasing. The spike was attributed to local firecrackers and a sharp rise in pollutants from stubble burning, accounting for 27% of Delhi's pollution on that day.
title: Delhi sees season’s first smog on Diwali, farm fire share in pollution rises: CSE

description: The Diwali releases saw strong box office performance over the holiday period, with both Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 and Singham Again reporting significant earnings. Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 is trending positively and is expected to achieve similar or slightly higher figures than Friday. Singham Again may see a slight dip or maintain similar numbers by the end of the day.
title: Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3: Kartik Aaryan's film earns over Rs 36 crore on day 2

description: Rohit Shetty's Diwali release, Singham Again, has made a strong start at the box office. The film, featuring Ajay Devgn, Akshay Kumar, Ranveer Singh, Deepika Padukone, and Arjun Kapoor, among others, faced competition from Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 starring Kartik Aaryan, Vidya Balan, Madhuri Dixit, and Triptii Dimri. According to Sacnilk, Singham Again earned Rs 43.5 crore on its opening day. The movie saw a slight dip on Saturday but still collected around Rs 41.5 crore, bringing its two-day total to Rs 85 crore, as per early estimates.
title: Singham Again box office collection day 2: Rohit Shetty's film earns over Rs 41 crore

description: National Green Tribunal (NGT) has directed the Union environment ministry and other authorities to respond to a report detailing the severe lack of infrastructure for forest fire management in Uttarakhand. The report highlights issues such as insufficient firefighting equipment, communication devices, and inadequate staffing, presenting critical hurdles to effective wildfire control in the state.
title: Uttarakhand lacks infrastructure to fight forest fires, NGT told

description: A high-level Indian delegation, led by PM's principal secretary PK Mishra, attended the G-20 Disaster Risk Reduction Working Group ministerial meeting in Belem, Brazil. Mishra emphasized international collaboration for disaster resilience and highlighted India's priorities, including early warning systems, resilient infrastructure, and financing. Key meetings were held with ministers from Brazil, South Africa, Japan, and other nations.
title: PM aide bats for international synergy at disaster risk reduction meet

description: India has significantly reduced TB incidence by 18% from 2015 to 2023, surpassing the global decline of 8%. The WHO report credits the country's decentralised healthcare efforts and a substantial budget increase for the TB program. Additionally, new treatments and AI-enabled diagnostics are being introduced to further combat the disease.
title: Tuberculosis cases dip 18% during '15-'23, WHO pats India

description: Former Philadelphia Eagles Center Jason Kelce confronted a Penn State fan outside Beaver Studio who hurled a homophobic slur at his brother Travis. Jason smashed the man's phone in retaliation, sparking debate on social media about whether his reaction was justified. "This is exactly how trolls should be handled in real life. Kudos to Jason Kelce," a post said.
title: Jason Kelce smashes fan's phone for attack on Travis, Taylor Swift: 'Who's the f***** now?'

description: Shubman Gill's century against England in Vizag marked his return to form after a challenging start to 2024. His mindset against spin paid off, leading to significant contributions, including a crucial 90-run knock against New Zealand. Gill emphasized focusing on long batting sessions without the pressure of runs to rediscover the joy in batting.
title: Tried to replicate what I did right against England: Shubman Gill

description: The Canadian Centre for Cyber Security's National Cyber Threat Assessment 2025-2026 highlights state-sponsored cyber threats, naming India for the first time alongside China, Russia, Iran, and North Korea. Canadian-Indian relations have deteriorated, leading to India's rejection of the cyber espionage accusations as part of Canada's strategy to malign it.
title: Canada's National Cyber Threat Assessment that blames India of 'likely spying'
Tragedies while making reels in UP: 2 run over by train, 1 feared drowned
'We are not Kukis': Manipur community rejects British-era tag
Newborn thrown off bridge and stuck on tree survives 50 wounds
‘Verification patrolling’ has begun in Depsang too: Government
'Sabka sath, sabka vikas' a mockery of fight for social justice, says Congress

description: Investigators are cracking down on the Bambiha syndicate by identifying their operational areas and members. The syndicate's presence has been marked by violent acts, including shootings and murders, in various regions. Retaliation from rival gangs is anticipated. The dossier details alliances and past criminal activities linked to the gang.
title: 100 members, 4 states: How Bambihas grew as a gang

description: Delhi Police crime branch arrested Vishnuswaroop Shahi, the mastermind behind the May murder of Dr Yogesh Chander Paul, near the Indo-Nepal border. Shahi, who evaded capture by changing identities and locations, was implicated through mobile records and his accomplices' confessions. The crime was planned with inside information from the doctor's domestic helper and involved robbery.
title: False identities, new mobiles, fake SIMs: How doctor’s murderer evaded cops for months

description: New Delhi experienced a brief improvement in air quality on Saturday morning due to consistent winds, but pollution worsened later in the day as winds calmed and stubble burning from other states increased. The AQI reached 'very poor' levels, and further deterioration is expected due to unfavorable meteorological conditions.
title: Delhi air pollution: Wind speed dips, farm fires hit AQI

description: Two individuals, Anuj Kumar, 20, and Ranjeet Kumar, 16, were fatally struck by the Humsafar Express train while creating social media reels on a railway track in Etawah district. Residents notified police who identified the victims via their footwear. The duo, painters in Ahmedabad, had returned home for Diwali. Legal procedures are underway.
title: 2 youths shooting reels on railway track run over by train in Uttar Pradesh
